transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Are you there?

Speaker 1: Yes. How are we doing? Mr. Sperry?

Speaker 2: Yeah, that's me.

Speaker 1: Yeah, Robert Sperry. How can I help you, sir?

Speaker 2: Um, somehow you guys charged my account again for the $413 or something.

Speaker 1: When I was canceled, I just wanted four tablets from the last purchase, and that was it.

Speaker 2: Oh, oh, okay, okay, gotcha.

Speaker 1: I already called my bank and stopped it, but I wanted to let you guys know because you just charged my account here a couple hours ago.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so it was related to the prescription because usually when the doctor writes it, when you have low quantity, they write it every 30 days.

Speaker 1: Unless you say you don't need it, now we pause or we stop, you know what I'm saying?

Speaker 2: Like, you just come with the prescription initially.

Speaker 1: Okay, well, I don't want any more, so don't ship it to me.

Speaker 2: Okay, I'm going to cancel and refund you that order here.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: And I canceled your account as well.

Speaker 1: Just be advised in case the price is up in the future because they're going to have to get you a new doctor or consultation.

Speaker 2: Just cancel everything, brother. Just cancel everything, please.

Speaker 1: Yeah, that's what I did, and I refunded you the refill, the 400. I just refunded you right now.

Speaker 2: All right, thanks for your service, man. You guys are cool. That was fast.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay. Thank you.

Speaker 2: Have a great day.

Speaker 1: You too. Bye-bye.
